A son of the Ohinoyi of Ebiraland in Kogi State, Prince Malik Ado-Ibrahim, has emerged as the presidential candidate of the Young Progressive Party (YPP). A businessman and founder of the Reset Nigeria Initiative, Prince Malik, with 66 votes defeated his closest rival, Mrs. Ruby Isaac who garnered 4 votes. While there were 74 accredited delegates, only 70 voted. In his acceptance speech, Ado-Ibrahim, urged Nigerians to put away religious and ethnic diversity for collective development. 